<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFRovere1959">Rovere, Richard H. (1959). <i>Senator Joe McCarthy</i>. University of California Press. pp.&#160;79. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0520204727" class="internal">ISBN 0-520-20472-7</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Senator+Joe+McCarthy&amp;rft.aulast=Rovere&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard+H.&amp;rft.au=Rovere%2C+Richard+H.&amp;rft.date=1959&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B79&amp;rft.pub=University+of+California+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-520-20472-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Joseph_McCarthy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> In <i>A Conspiracy So Immense,</i> Oshinsky states that McCarthy chose Marquette University rather than the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Wisconsin-Madison" title="University of Wisconsin-Madison">University of Wisconsin-Madison</a> partially because Marquette was under Catholic control and partially because he enrolled during the Great Depression, when few working-class or farm-bred students had the money to go out of state for college. <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFOshinsky2005">Oshinsky, David M. (2005). <i>A Conspiracy So Immense: The World of Joe McCarthy</i>. Oxford University Press. pp.&#160;11. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/019515424X" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-515424-X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Conspiracy+So+Immense%3A+The+World+of+Joe+McCarthy&amp;rft.aulast=Oshinsky&amp;rft.aufirst=David+M.&amp;rft.au=Oshinsky%2C+David+M.&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B11&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-19-515424-X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Joseph_McCarthy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> Oshinsky explains this (p. 17) as resulting partially from the financial pressures of the Great Depression. He also notes (p. 28) that even during his judgeship, McCarthy was known to have gambled heavily after hours. <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFOshinsky2005">Oshinsky, David M. (2005). <i>A Conspiracy So Immense: The World of Joe McCarthy</i>. Oxford University Press. pp.&#160;17, 28. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/019515424X" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-515424-X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Conspiracy+So+Immense%3A+The+World+of+Joe+McCarthy&amp;rft.aulast=Oshinsky&amp;rft.aufirst=David+M.&amp;rft.au=Oshinsky%2C+David+M.&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B17%2C+28&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-19-515424-X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Joseph_McCarthy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFOshinsky2005">Oshinsky, David M. (2005). <i>A Conspiracy So Immense: The World of Joe McCarthy</i>. Oxford University Press. pp.&#160;27. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/019515424X" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-515424-X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Conspiracy+So+Immense%3A+The+World+of+Joe+McCarthy&amp;rft.aulast=Oshinsky&amp;rft.aufirst=David+M.&amp;rft.au=Oshinsky%2C+David+M.&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B27&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-19-515424-X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Joseph_McCarthy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Arthur1-9">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Arthur1_9-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Arthur1_9-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHerman1999">Herman, Arthur (1999). <i>Joseph McCarthy: Reexamining the Life and Legacy of America's Most Hated Senator</i>. Free Press. pp.&#160;30. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0684836254" class="internal">ISBN 0-684-83625-4</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joseph+McCarthy%3A+Reexamining+the+Life+and+Legacy+of+America%27s+Most+Hated+Senator&amp;rft.aulast=Herman&amp;rft.aufirst=Arthur&amp;rft.au=Herman%2C+Arthur&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B30&amp;rft.pub=Free+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-684-83625-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Joseph_McCarthy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> Oshinsky describes the nickname "Tail-Gunner Joe" as the result of McCarthy's wish to break the record for most live ammunition discharged in a single mission. <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFOshinsky2005">Oshinsky, David M. (2005). <i>A Conspiracy So Immense: The World of Joe McCarthy</i>. Oxford University Press. pp.&#160;32. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/019515424X" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-515424-X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Conspiracy+So+Immense%3A+The+World+of+Joe+McCarthy&amp;rft.aulast=Oshinsky&amp;rft.aufirst=David+M.&amp;rft.au=Oshinsky%2C+David+M.&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B32&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-19-515424-X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Joseph_McCarthy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFMorgan2003">Morgan, Ted (November/December 2003), <i><a href="http://www.legalaffairs.org/issues/November-December-2003/story_morgan_novdec03.msp" class="external text" title="http://www.legalaffairs.org/issues/November-December-2003/story_morgan_novdec03.msp" rel="nofollow">Judge Joe; How the youngest judge in Wisconsin's history became the country's most notorious senator.</a></i>, Legal Affairs<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.legalaffairs.org/issues/November-December-2003/story_morgan_novdec03.msp" class="external free" title="http://www.legalaffairs.org/issues/November-December-2003/story_morgan_novdec03.msp" rel="nofollow">http://www.legalaffairs.org/issues/November-December-2003/story_morgan_novdec03.msp</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2006-08-02</span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Judge+Joe%3B+How+the+youngest+judge+in+Wisconsin%27s+history+became+the+country%27s+most+notorious+senator.&amp;rft.aulast=Morgan&amp;rft.aufirst=Ted&amp;rft.au=Morgan%2C+Ted&amp;rft.date=November%2FDecember+2003&amp;rft.pub=Legal+Affairs&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.legalaffairs.org%2Fissues%2FNovember-December-2003%2Fstory_morgan_novdec03.msp&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Joseph_McCarthy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
